============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the speed of light?
A1: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

Q2: What is relativity?
A2: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q3: What is the water cycle?
A3: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q4: What is gravity?
A4: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q5: What is the Renaissance?
A5: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

